I'll spit on floors

07:30.450 --> 07:32.352
And do more drugs

07:32.452 --> 07:34.354
Burn every bill

07:34.454 --> 07:36.356
Get drunk on love

07:36.456 --> 07:38.483
Wear next to nothing...

07:38.583 --> 07:41.778
Hey, Frankie, sweetheart! Hey, Frankie!

07:41.878 --> 07:44.114
Let's get out of here.
I got work in the morning. I'm trashed.

07:44.214 --> 07:46.616
Are you too tired to go home with me?

07:46.716 --> 07:48.493
I might be tired, but I'm not dead.

07:48.593 --> 07:50.871
I'll be uncareful

07:50.971 --> 07:52.497
I'll cause such scenes

07:52.597 --> 07:54.583
And I'll never talk

07:54.683 --> 07:56.585
Of used-to-bes

07:56.685 --> 07:58.754
Tattoo my face

07:58.854 --> 08:00.881
I won't go grey

08:00.981 --> 08:02.424
Be a dancing queen

08:02.524 --> 08:05.594
I'm growing old disgracefully

08:05.694 --> 08:08.847
I'm so up and down

08:08.947 --> 08:12.559
And I love what's not allowed

08:12.659 --> 08:14.561
I was lost

08:14.661 --> 08:17.147
Now I see

08:17.247 --> 08:22.903
And now I'm growing old disgracefully.

09:23.021 --> 09:24.423
Oh, hi, Mom.

09:24.523 --> 09:26.800
How do you do that?
How did you know that was me?

09:26.900 --> 09:28.009
Of course it's you.

09:28.109 --> 09:30.220
You have the most persistent
ring I know.

09:30.320 --> 09:32.806
Well, I just wanted to say hi
while I'm near a phone.

09:32.906 --> 09:35.267
- How are you?
- Where are you anyway?

09:35.367 --> 09:36.768
Belo Quinto, near Rio.

09:36.868 --> 09:37.978
- It's beautiful...
- Mom, hold on.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.188
I'm getting another call.

09:40.288 --> 09:41.398
Hello?

09:41.498 --> 09:42.774
It's about time. Where you been, baby?

09:42.874 --> 09:45.610
Ha, ha. I hate it when you just leave.

09:45.710 --> 09:47.112
You could at least say good-bye.

09:47.212 --> 09:49.364
- Why?
- "Why"?

09:49.464 --> 09:50.657
Forget it.

09:50.757 --> 09:53.243
Look, I got my mom on the other line
long distance.

09:53.343 --> 09:55.413
- I'll see you tonight.
- All right, I'll see you later.

09:56.513 --> 10:00.125
Mom? Hi, I'm back.
So how do you like Rio?

10:00.225 --> 10:02.586
It was great. Did you get my package?

10:02.686 --> 10:04.296
Yeah, I got it yesterday.

10:04.396 --> 10:06.006
Well, what did you think?
Did you like it?

10:06.106 --> 10:08.968
- Did you open it yet?
- Hold on, I'm gonna change phones.

10:15.991 --> 10:17.100
Well, what do you think?

10:17.200 --> 10:18.643
Did you get a chance
to look at everything?

10:18.743 --> 10:20.520
- I'm opening it now.
- Uh-huh, and?

10:20.620 --> 10:23.815
- Ooh! Ah, pretty postcards.
- Aren't those pretty?

10:23.915 --> 10:26.193
- Cute brush.
- I saw a lady make that.

10:26.293 --> 10:27.986
- A little hat.
- The ha... isn't that cute?

10:28.086 --> 10:30.405
- It's for a little doll or something.
- A necklace.

10:30.505 --> 10:33.617
Well, no, it's not really a necklace.
It's a rosary.

10:33.717 --> 10:34.826
Where'd you get it?

10:34.926 --> 10:36.453
This little village called Belo Quinto.

10:36.553 --> 10:39.581
- I didn't even know you went there.
- I took a little side trip over here.

10:39.681 --> 10:41.583
So what do you think of the presents?
Do you love 'em?

10:41.683 --> 10:43.668
I'm so glad I got a chance
to talk to you.

10:43.768 --> 10:45.837
I'm going on that cruise.
I'm not gonna talk to you for a month.

10:45.937 --> 10:47.881
- And I have to run.
- Okay, have fun. I love you.

10:47.981 --> 10:50.259
- I love you, too, sweetie, bye-bye.
- I'm glad you called, Mom. Bye.

11:10.211 --> 11:12.280
Can I get two lattes, please? Low-fat.

11:12.380 --> 11:14.533
- Yeah, got it.
- Just one. You know, I'm okay.

11:14.633 --> 11:16.577
Let me get
a bacon and egg sandwich, too.

11:17.719 --> 11:19.246
- To go.
- Coming up.

11:19.346 --> 11:20.789
What's up? You're not eating today?

11:20.889 --> 11:22.874
I threw up this morning
from the smell of tea.

11:22.974 --> 11:24.292
Oh, God.

11:24.392 --> 11:25.544
Late?

11:25.644 --> 11:27.921
- Like, a week.
- A week?

11:28.021 --> 11:30.799
I don't know, a few days.
Kinda feel weird.

11:30.899 --> 11:32.510
You're so dramatic.

11:34.653 --> 11:36.596
I think you're just
psyching yourself out.

11:36.696 --> 11:41.079
I feel like my heart
went to go live in my stomach.

11:41.179 --> 11:43.270
Okay, it's not dramatic.

11:43.370 --> 11:45.355
- What if I'm having a baby?
- With Steven?

11:45.455 --> 11:47.232
What if I'm bringing a person
into this world?

11:47.332 --> 11:49.568
Man, what if? You've got options.

11:49.668 --> 11:50.819
You know what?
I don't want to think about it.

11:50.919 --> 11:52.737
- It's making me cranky.
- Here's your to-go.

11:52.837 --> 11:54.447
You know what,
let's get our tired asses to work...

11:54.547 --> 11:56.408
- Thanks. Hold this.
- ...'cause we are late.

11:56.508 --> 11:58.410
You're always late. There's nothing new.

12:59.195 --> 13:01.514
Father Andrew Kiernan, welcome back.

13:01.614 --> 13:02.891
Cardinal Houseman.

13:02.991 --> 13:05.352
These are interesting. What's the trick?

13:05.452 --> 13:07.896
Well, to be honest, I don't know.

13:07.996 --> 13:10.231
They probably made a fortune out of her.

13:10.331 --> 13:12.817
And, uh, what's... what was this?

13:12.917 --> 13:14.402
Infrared photographs of tears.

13:14.502 --> 13:16.863
The statue is made of stone,
therefore room temperature.

13:16.963 --> 13:19.574
But the tears show up
as white because, um...

13:19.674 --> 13:21.660
because they're warm.

13:21.760 --> 13:24.913
- Warm tears?
- Yes.

13:25.013 --> 13:27.415
My lab report and analysis confirm

13:27.515 --> 13:31.378
that the blood from the statue
is not only warm, but human.

13:34.647 --> 13:36.091
I know what you're thinking.

13:36.191 --> 13:38.885
But with all due respect, Daniel,
this isn't a fake.

13:38.985 --> 13:40.720
It's a freestanding mass of solid stone.

13:40.820 --> 13:42.514
And there is no scientific explanation.

13:42.614 --> 13:45.016
Andrew, it's my understanding
you were sent to Brazil

13:45.116 --> 13:47.602
in order to investigate the appearance
of the Virgin Mary

13:47.702 --> 13:48.895
on the side of a building.

13:48.995 --> 13:51.981
Yes, but while I was in Sao Paulo,
I heard about the statue,

13:52.081 --> 13:53.692
- so I decided to go and investigate.
- And?

13:53.792 --> 13:54.984
And what?

13:55.084 --> 13:56.486
The face of the Virgin Mary
on the building.

13:56.586 --> 14:00.740
It's an oxidation stain
caused by rainwater

14:00.840 --> 14:02.575
running down untreated side walls,

14:02.675 --> 14:05.078
causes an optical illusion
of a veiled woman.

14:05.178 --> 14:07.747
Good.
We'll consider the matter closed, then.

14:07.847 --> 14:10.959
Father Dario has your next assignment.

14:11.059 --> 14:14.671
I was hoping that perhaps
you could send me back to, um...

14:14.771 --> 14:16.297
to Belo Quinto.

14:16.397 --> 14:17.507
Why?

14:17.607 --> 14:20.593
Because I need to do
some more tests on the statue.

14:20.693 --> 14:23.388
You're telling me you left the statue
in Belo Quinto?

14:23.488 --> 14:24.973
Yes.

14:25.073 --> 14:26.641
I was going to take it back, obviously,

14:26.741 --> 14:29.310
but when I saw the effect that it had
on the people... it's amazing.

14:29.410 --> 14:32.939
It's become almost like
a cornerstone of their faith.

14:33.039 --> 14:36.401
Andrew, the cornerstone
of their faith is the Church,

14:36.501 --> 14:38.111
not a crying statue.

14:38.211 --> 14:39.696
When you're in the field,

14:39.796 --> 14:41.823
you're a representative
of the Catholic Church

14:41.923 --> 14:43.992
and the Congregation
of the Causes of the Saints.

14:44.092 --> 14:45.744
Yes, I'm very well aware
of that, Daniel.

14:45.844 --> 14:48.955
I am also a scientist
and I observe the facts.

14:49.055 --> 14:52.667
And the facts are that this statue
has tears of blood.

14:52.767 --> 14:55.795
Well, if that's the case,
you know the policy.

14:55.895 --> 14:58.131
The statue is brought back
to the Vatican.

14:58.231 --> 14:59.924
We conduct expert tests...

15:00.024 --> 15:03.136
geologists, engineers,
medical examiners.

15:03.236 --> 15:07.307
We've examined 50 or 60 crying statues
in the last 12 months.

15:07.407 --> 15:08.808
Not a single one of them
has turned out...

15:08.908 --> 15:11.853
Yes, I'm very well aware of that,
but I just wanted you to know

15:11.953 --> 15:15.774
that in my opinion,
I think that this is different.

15:15.874 --> 15:18.318
I'm not going to allow you
to go back to Brazil.

15:18.418 --> 15:21.112
We'll get a geologist down there,
and if he sees fit,

15:21.212 --> 15:23.531
we'll get the statue sent back
for further tests.

15:23.631 --> 15:25.492
Father Dario, get me
all the information you can

15:25.592 --> 15:27.994
on this church in Belo Quinto,
would you?

15:28.094 --> 15:30.414
Thank you, Andrew.

15:32.015 --> 15:33.625
Thank you.

15:42.775 --> 15:45.303
I have never seen him this way before.

15:45.403 --> 15:48.681
Andrew's problem is he can't decide
if he's a scientist or a priest.

15:53.161 --> 15:54.270
Frankie, come on.

15:54.370 --> 15:57.148
- You are gonna drive yourself crazy.
- No.

15:57.248 --> 15:58.650
If you're worried about being pregnant,

15:58.750 --> 16:01.486
why don't we go to the store
right now and get a test?

16:01.586 --> 16:03.279
Well, let's just give it
a couple of days, okay?

16:03.379 --> 16:04.572
- Are you sure?
- I'm fine.

16:04.672 --> 16:06.115
And stop mothering me. Yes.

16:06.215 --> 16:08.785
All right, girlfriend.
I'll call you later.

16:08.885 --> 16:10.996
Okay, bye. Drive safe.

16:37.872 --> 16:39.607
- Late?
- Like, a week.

16:39.707 --> 16:42.902
You're always late. There's nothing new.

16:43.002 --> 16:45.154
What if I'm bringing
a person into this world?

16:45.254 --> 16:47.324
Frankie, you've got options.

18:54.717 --> 18:57.286
Nurse, somebody needs
to tell me what's going on.

18:57.386 --> 18:59.664
- I don't understand.
- Get out of the way!

18:59.764 --> 19:02.208
Frankie, can you hear me?
I'm right here with you.

19:02.308 --> 19:03.751
Let's go!

19:03.851 --> 19:06.212
I don't understand
why there's so much blood.

19:06.312 --> 19:07.755
- Get me a clamp right now.
- Frankie!

19:07.855 --> 19:10.883
All right, CBC, electrolytes,
UA, tox screen.

19:13.569 --> 19:14.721
Get me a pulse ox, STAT!

19:14.821 --> 19:17.557
- Get me a tox screen and a STAT CT.
- Right away.

19:17.657 --> 19:18.975
Heart rate is irregular.

19:19.075 --> 19:22.186
Blood pressure's off the map.
195 over 120.

19:22.286 --> 19:24.397
- Let's change cuffs.
- Where's the IV?

19:33.047 --> 19:35.658
I'm calling it, code blue!
Get the paddles.

19:35.758 --> 19:37.201
Get some gel. Okay, ready?

19:37.301 --> 19:40.121
- Mark, get the paddle.
- All right, clear!

19:40.221 --> 19:42.623
Temperature and blood pressure
are back to normal.

19:44.934 --> 19:46.252
Who are you?

19:46.352 --> 19:49.422
I'm Dr. Reston.
Do you know what your name is?

19:49.522 --> 19:51.257
What happened? Where am I?

19:51.357 --> 19:52.842
You're in the emergency room.

19:52.942 --> 19:55.011
You were found unconscious
in your apartment.

19:55.111 --> 19:57.263
- Do you remember anything?
- No.

19:57.363 --> 20:00.516
Oh, Jesus.
Can I get some more help over here?

20:00.616 --> 20:03.686
We need some four-by-fours.
We have a very deep laceration here.

20:03.786 --> 20:06.272
Oh, my God, it's gone right through.

20:06.372 --> 20:07.732
Miss, you can't go in there.

20:07.832 --> 20:09.442
- I'm sorry, Doctor, I just need to...
- Please have a seat.

20:09.542 --> 20:11.110
I just need to know
what's going on with her.

20:11.210 --> 20:13.322
She'll be fine.
Please have a seat. Thank you.

20:15.715 --> 20:19.327
These are puncture wounds, Frankie,
caused by the entry of a sharp object.

20:19.427 --> 20:20.953
Are you in any pain?

20:21.053 --> 20:23.873
No. That's weird, isn't it?

20:23.973 --> 20:27.460
Wow, will you look at that?
It only bleeds when I touch it.

20:27.560 --> 20:29.087
Maybe you should not touch it.

20:29.187 --> 20:32.006
Both wounds are identical...
the same size, same shape.

20:32.106 --> 20:35.009
She missed the main artery
by less than a centimeter.

20:35.109 --> 20:37.346
You keep saying "she,"
but I didn't do this.

20:39.238 --> 20:41.432
What's happening in your life, Frankie?

20:41.532 --> 20:43.351
Do you have a lot of stress at work?

20:43.451 --> 20:45.186
I cut hair.

20:45.286 --> 20:48.189
Do you have any trouble
with a significant other?

20:48.289 --> 20:50.608
- Yes.
- And that is?

20:50.708 --> 20:52.652
I'm not very significant.

20:53.878 --> 20:56.072
Look, how long is this gonna take?
I wanna go home.

20:56.172 --> 20:58.741
I think you should stay here
at least 24 hours for observation.

20:58.841 --> 21:01.369
- We need to get a handle on this.
- There's nothing to get a handle on.

21:01.469 --> 21:03.621
Frankie, I'm not gonna kid you...
with wounds like this,

21:03.721 --> 21:06.916
it's pretty obvious
that they were self-inflicted.

21:07.016 --> 21:08.418
You think I did this?

21:09.560 --> 21:12.004
It would never happen.

21:12.104 --> 21:15.800
I love being me. Ask anyone.

21:32.500 --> 21:36.196
Frankie, turn the light off, honey,
and come to bed.

21:44.553 --> 21:47.665
Do you smell flowers
in here or something?

21:48.265 --> 21:50.877
No.

21:50.977 --> 21:54.089
Smells like jasmine
or hyacinth or something.

21:55.690 --> 21:57.592
I don't smell anything.

21:58.985 --> 22:02.471
Mmm. You need anything?

22:02.571 --> 22:04.015
No.

22:05.116 --> 22:08.478
- Good night.
- Good night.

22:32.226 --> 22:34.504
Grazie, signore.

22:37.565 --> 22:38.925
Duty-free.

22:40.860 --> 22:43.596
- Welcome back, Andrew.
- Gianni, come stai?

22:43.696 --> 22:46.724
Sto bene. Ah, God is good.

22:46.824 --> 22:48.726
So how was Belo Quinto?

22:48.826 --> 22:51.646
How do you know about Belo Quinto?
I was sent to Sao Paulo.

22:51.746 --> 22:54.065
God lives here, remember?
We know everything.

22:54.165 --> 22:56.817
- Oh, yes, I forgot.
- So how are you doing?

22:57.617 --> 22:59.528
I don't know.

22:59.628 --> 23:01.739
I don't know.

23:01.839 --> 23:06.535
I travel round the world
investigating miracles.

23:06.635 --> 23:08.120
And then I disprove them.

23:08.220 --> 23:10.581
The real miracle
is anybody believes anything.

23:10.681 --> 23:13.334
I don't know what I'm doing,
to tell you the truth.

23:13.434 --> 23:15.544
None of us know what we are doing.

23:15.644 --> 23:18.172
- So what are you working on?
- I have no idea.

23:18.272 --> 23:21.478
Well, how can you translate something
if you've no idea?

23:21.578 --> 23:23.094
I'm a linguist, Andrew.

23:23.194 --> 23:25.596
I translate words, not their relevance.

23:25.696 --> 23:28.307
But this one is a second century gospel.

23:28.407 --> 23:30.017
How many is that you're up to now?

23:30.117 --> 23:32.895
I've helped translate about 15.

23:32.995 --> 23:35.523
That only leaves 20 still to go.

23:35.623 --> 23:38.985
So there are, what, 35 gospels?

23:39.085 --> 23:41.487
Everyone had a different experience
of Jesus,

23:41.587 --> 23:43.781
so they all wrote different stories.

23:43.881 --> 23:47.118
You see, all the gospels,
they're interpretations.

23:47.218 --> 23:51.330
They're memories, dreams, reflections.

23:51.430 --> 23:55.001
And there's no one gospel
in Jesus' actual words?

23:55.101 --> 23:57.878
We're all blind men in a cave

23:57.978 --> 24:02.174
looking for a candle
that was lit 2,000 years ago.

24:02.274 --> 24:03.968
So what's in this text?

24:04.068 --> 24:07.596
- I was only given every third page.
- Why?

24:07.696 --> 24:12.059
The most sensitive documents are always
divided into threes among us...

24:12.159 --> 24:15.062
one-third to the Dominicans,
one-third to the Franciscans,

24:15.162 --> 24:17.356
and one-third to us Jesuits.

24:17.456 --> 24:22.403
The truth of any document
is only known to a very powerful few.

24:22.503 --> 24:24.906
That's typical of this place, isn't it?

24:26.173 --> 24:29.869
We live in a highly competitive
world, Andrew.

24:29.969 --> 24:32.831
- The Church is no exception.
- Hmm.

24:34.014 --> 24:36.709
Nothing ever gets out of here, does it?

24:36.809 --> 24:39.587
Unless, of course, they want it to.

24:43.107 --> 24:46.761
Both wounds are identical...
same size, same shape.

24:46.861 --> 24:49.263
She missed the main artery
by less than a centimeter.

24:49.363 --> 24:51.098
You think I did this?

24:51.198 --> 24:53.351
What's happening in your life, Frankie?

25:01.167 --> 25:03.110
So, Jen, tell us about your date.

25:03.210 --> 25:04.862
It was with a tax lawyer.

25:04.962 --> 25:07.031
- A tax lawyer?
- Yeah.

25:07.131 --> 25:08.824
But when I first met him,
he seemed really cool.

25:08.924 --> 25:11.494
- Hey.
- Hey, hi, guys.

25:11.594 --> 25:12.787
- Hey, Frankie.
- How you feeling?

25:12.887 --> 25:14.331
Fine.

25:17.850 --> 25:19.460
Really okay or just okay?

25:19.560 --> 25:21.379
I'm fine.

25:21.479 --> 25:22.713
So how's my day looking?

25:22.813 --> 25:25.633
Well, I started your first client,
and you're booked solid until 7:00.

25:25.733 --> 25:27.093
Thanks.

25:27.193 --> 25:28.386
Wanna come over here?

25:28.486 --> 25:30.304
Okay, well, go back to Jen
and dish the dirt.

25:32.990 --> 25:36.102
So, uh, he seemed pretty cool.

25:36.202 --> 25:39.105
Divorced, but no kids.

25:39.205 --> 25:42.566
But he left the table
in the middle of dinner

25:42.666 --> 25:44.777
to call his mother in Oregon.

25:44.877 --> 25:47.238
Major points for the long-distance mom.

25:47.338 --> 25:50.866
Yeah. You know,
I thought I'd give him a shot.

25:50.966 --> 25:53.452
But you won't believe what he did.

25:53.552 --> 25:57.289
Every single time he took
a bite of his steak...

25:57.389 --> 25:58.791
he growled.

25:58.891 --> 26:00.251
He growled!

26:55.030 --> 26:56.307
Shit!

26:56.407 --> 26:58.184
Stop! There's a baby!

26:58.978 --> 27:00.519
Frankie!

27:00.619 --> 27:02.688
- Stop! Wait!
- Hey, lady!

27:02.788 --> 27:06.108
